1. One-Time Setup (Sirf shuru mein ek baar)
Jab aapne naya project shuru kiya tha aur libraries install karni thi.

Libraries Install karna:

PowerShell

pip install customtkinter pillow
PyInstaller Install karna (EXE banane ke liye):

PowerShell

pip install pyinstaller
2. Daily Workflow (Development ke dauran)
Jab aap code likh rahe hote hain aur test karna chahte hain.

C Code (Backend) Compile karna: (Jab bhi C code change karein)

PowerShell

gcc backend/main.c backend/cipher.c -o bin/encryptor.exe
Python App Test karna (Bina EXE banaye): (Jab Python code change karein)

PowerShell

python frontend/app.py
3. Final Production (Software Launch) üöÄ
Jab aap software final karke dost ko bhejna chahte hain.

Python ka Final EXE banana (Icon aur Assets ke saath): (Yeh command sabse important hai)

PowerShell

python -m PyInstaller --noconsole --onefile --icon "assets/icon.ico" --add-data "assets;assets" frontend/app.py
Engine (C Code) ko Final Folder me Copy karna: (PyInstaller ke baad ye zarur karna hai)

PowerShell

if (!(Test-Path dist\bin)) { mkdir dist\bin }; cp bin\encryptor.exe dist\bin\ -Force
4. Running the App (Terminal se)
Agar aap double-click nahi karna chahte.

Final App Chalana:

PowerShell

./dist/app.exe
üìù Summary: Project update karne ka Sahi Order
Jab bhi aap code update karein, bas ye 3 commands line se chalayein:

Compile Engine: gcc backend/main.c backend/cipher.c -o bin/encryptor.exe

Build App: python -m PyInstaller --noconsole --onefile --icon "assets/icon.ico" --add-data "assets;assets" frontend/app.py

Copy Engine: if (!(Test-Path dist\bin)) { mkdir dist\bin }; cp bin\encryptor.exe dist\bin\ -Force